This is a blog.
A blog to commemorate the gods.
The gods of my town.
When i post this entry, you will think im full of it.  And that other people were better than us...and you can thnk what you want.  Lasts ummer a group was formed, a group called the Chemical Union.  A pained group, and a troubled bunch.  Last summer we owned medina.  Constantly walking the streets and never backing down from a fight, even when the odds are seven to three.  As it always turns out, the seven backed down.  Last summer the old form of the chemical union intook more drugs then we like to speak of.  The old form being Nikki, Steve, Josh, and myself.  Since then we have been threw some hard times, steve and josh were fighting, nikki wasnt even communicating anymore, and it was time to oust her.  Later after I moved there were three of us, all located in different towns. Noone knew later, that none other than dan flatt would fill the empty fourth spot.  Since flattacular has joined the cu i have had some of the best times in my life, that i would neevr trade for anything.  Just recently the news came that Josh was moving, to north carolina.  This is just another challenge we have to face.  One thing i always want you guys to know, is that you are brothers to me, and i will always be there for oyu, untill we are buried on the same grounds.  I miss you guys an unbelievable amount.  I know nothing will come between us, and I know the legends of some of the crazy shit we did will never die.  Because we are the mighty Chemical Union.

You know those days.  I wont ever forget that summer, all the days with josh and steve.  I really will miss it this summer.  I mean look at whats happening to us, Josh, moving to one of the carolinas, steve, out in albany, im here, In red creek, and Flatt is still at home representing medina.
